# Cloudflare Pages redirects.
#
# IMPORTANT — precedence rules:
#   - 200 "rewrite" is processed BEFORE static files (would hijack
#     existing SSG pages). DO NOT use 200 for this fallback.
#   - 301/302 "redirect" is processed ONLY when no static match exists.
#     That's what we want here.
#
# Reviews added to R2 after the last site build don't have a SSG page
# at /review/{id}/. For those, 302-redirect to the legacy client-fetch
# route so the page still loads (URL changes to /review/?id={id}, and
# share preview falls back to the generic title — accepted tradeoff
# for R2-only updates). See README.md "Iron rule".
#
# Reviews already SSG'd (in git at last build) are served as static
# files and this rule is skipped for them.
/review/:id/  /review/?id=:id  302
